Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with primitive digraphs and infinite series of synchronizing automata, which are topics in discrete mathematics.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as synchronizing automata are related to control systems and the paper discusses the minimum length of reset words.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with automata and their synchronization properties.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper may involve logical reasoning in proving properties of the automata and digraphs.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with data structures or algorithms, but may involve some algorithmic techniques in analyzing the automata and digraphs.
